Detailed Description

cvmx_sriomaint::_ir_sp_rx_data

This register is used to read data from the soft packet FIFO. The soft packet FIFO contains the majority of the packet data received from the SRIO link. The packet does not include the control symbols or the initial byte containing AckId, 2 reserved bits and the CRF. In the case of packets with less than 80 bytes (including AckId byte) both the trailing CRC and pad (if present) are included in the FIFO and octet count. In the case of a packet with exactly 80 bytes (including the AckId byte) the CRC is removed and the pad is maintained so the octet count will read 81 bytes instead of the expected 83. In cases over 80 bytes the CRC at 80 bytes is removed but the trailing CRC and Pad (if necessary) are present.
